Two brothers, who allegedly killed a teenage boy by cutting off his head for the purpose of selling it for a sum of N200,000, were yesterday arraigned before the Lagos High Court in Igbosere, Lagos. The brothers, Saheed Obadimeji, 19, and 20- year-old Ayodeji Obadimeji, are standing trial on a two-count charge of conspiracy to commit murder and murder. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY They pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Lagos State prosecutor, Mr Tunde Sunmonu, told the court that the defendants and others at large committed the alleged offences on November 27, 2018, by 8.30pm at an uncompleted building in Sapati town, Ibeju-Lekki, Lagos. Sunmonu said the defendants forcefully accosted the boy, Joseph Makinde, who was sent on errand by one of their neighbours, lured him into an uncompleted building and killed him. He added that the defendants intended to sell the boyâ€™s head, which they cut off, for N200,000. The prosecutor urged the court to remand the defendants in prison and called for a speedy trial. Truck conductors face trial over alleged murder Man kills neighbour with cutlass over generator smoke Teenager tells court how father was murdered over generator smoke